data.name: textBox6.Text
data.value:
Development Tools Only -- NEXT 25 ONLY --
This is for Roster Generation with internal imported spreadsheets. Recommend to avoid this unless you know what you're doing.
To Begin, Open a Roster Save and Load PLAY table. Then Import the 2024-PLAY-BASE.csv from the 2024-Roster-Base folder using DB Editor.
Then proceed the with the buttons in order. You can swap 2 and 3 if you want. It may give a different result!

data.name: textBoxOffSeason.Text
data.value:
This is the off-season toolbox for recruiting. These should be set at the beginning of Recruiting Phase
Raise Minimum Recruiting Points : This raises the min points and minimum allocation level (TRPA). The TRPA determines how many points are given each week, although it is just one of the many factors. The Min Points resets each week.
Modify Recruiting Interested Teams: This value is set to default of 10. If you lower it, there will be less teams automatically interested in a recruit. This allows other teams to try to get into the recruit's top 10 list.
Randomize Recruits: This randomizes the recruit attribute ratings. Use the tolerance to set the min/max randomization value. Weight and Height are also randomize. Potential, Injury and Awareness are also randomized. Recruit Star Ratings are NOT recalculated here. Run it separately!
Re-Calculate Recruiting/Transfer Ratings: Calculates recruiting ratings based on realistic recruiting scale from Rivals/247 Sports rankings. (Top 30 are 5 star, Top 300 are 4-star, Top 1000 are 3-star). Recruits and Transfers are rated separately.
Randomize Face & Skin: The game does not assign a random face shape to recruits by default. It will also randomize the skin tone and face type.
Randomize Recruit Names: This randomizes their first and last name from a database of 75K names
Randomize Walk-Ons: This randomizes the walk-on attribute ratings. Use the toleranace to set the min/max randomization value. Weight and Height are also randomize. Potential, Injury and Awareness are also randomized.
Polynesian Surname Generator: This changes recruits from Hawaii and western states to have polynesian surnames. The % Chance is for Hawaii, with 10-25% of CA, UT, WA, OR, AK, TX, CO, NV and AZ states getting players of polynesian descent.

data.name: dbToolsInfo.Text
data.value:
This is a set of NCAA Football Modding Tools that add more realism to the game.
Use these at the beginning of a season:
* Pre-Season Injuries - Randomly distributes injuries to players, with ability to have skill degradation.
Use these at the end of the Regular Season (or during Bowl Weeks)
* Medical Redshirt - Grants Players that have Season Ending injuries a redshirt year
It is recommended to use these tools after the completion of the National Championship game and before the start of the off-season.
* Body Size Progression - Randomly gives undersized freshman a boost in weight based on their potential rating to move them closer to the positional average. Max gain is 25lbs
* Coach Progression - Changes User/CPU Coach Prestige value based on performance. This is no longer required for NEXT 25+.
* Coaching Carousel - Fires and Hires Coaches automatically based on prestige and coaching score. Can also force transfers from teams that lose their head coach!
* Randomize Coaching Budgets - Randomizes the discipline, recruiting and training budgets for every coach
* Auto Realignment - This is a very primitive conference realignment algorithm based on regionality, prestige, and conference prestige.
* Players to Coach - This will convert high awareness graduating seniors to coaches.

data.name: textBox2.Text
data.value:
* Recalculate Player Overall - This will recalculate all players' overall rating based on the original game's POCI table
* Recalculate Team Ratings - Recalculates Team Ratings (Approximately)
* Body Size Fixer - This recalculates the body models for each player
* Calculate QB Tendencies - Re-Calculates QB for Scrambling, Balanced and Pocket Passers Traits
* Randomize Player Head/Face - Chooses a new face, head and hair for all players based on skin tone
* Randomize Player Potential - Randomizes from 40-99 every player's potential rating. Affects player progression.
* Unique Players - For Texture Modding Experts Only. Removes PSKI 1 and 4 for creation of unique player specific textures --
* Determine Impact Players - Picks 4 Impact Players in a Dynasty Save file based on overall (2 x Offense, 2 x Defense)
* Auto-Set Depth Chart - Creates a depth chart based on position ratings
* Fill Rosters - Generates random players to fill every team to 70, or until DB capacity runs out.
* Fantasy Roster Generator - Creates a fantasy roster for Roster or Dynasty saves. Will run through a series of modules.
